# CityU logo on HTML pages

Every HTML document in this project **must** show the City University of Hong Kong logo (`CityUHK_logo.png`) in the **top-left** corner of the viewport.

## Asset location

- Prefer **`CityUHK_logo.png` at the project repository root** so paths stay simple from top-level pages (`href="CityUHK_logo.png"` or `src="CityUHK_logo.png"`).
- For HTML files under subfolders, use a correct relative path (e.g. `../CityUHK_logo.png`) or copy the asset alongside that subtree if the build layout requires it—**do not** ship pages with a broken image path.

## Implementation

1. Add a single logo element (typically `<a href="…">` wrapping `<img>` for branding link, or plain `<img>` if no URL is desired).
2. Position it **fixed** (or equivalent) at **`top: 0; left: 0`** with padding/margin as needed so it does not touch viewport edges awkwardly (e.g. `top: 0.75rem; left: 0.75rem`).
3. Set **`alt`** text that describes the logo (e.g. `alt="City University of Hong Kong"`).
4. Constrain size so it does not dominate the layout (e.g. `max-height: 48px` or similar); preserve aspect ratio (`height: auto` with `width` or `max-*`).
5. Use a **`z-index`** high enough that the logo stays visible above page content (e.g. `z-index: 1000`).

## Example (inline CSS)

```html
<a class="cityu-brand" href="https://www.cityu.edu.hk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
  <img src="CityUHK_logo.png" alt="City University of Hong Kong" />
</a>
<style>
  .cityu-brand {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0.75rem;
    left: 0.75rem;
    z-index: 1000;
    line-height: 0;
  }
  .cityu-brand img {
    display: block;
    max-height: 48px;
    width: auto;
    height: auto;
  }
</style>
```

When creating or editing any `*.html` file, **add or preserve** this logo block unless the user explicitly opts out for a one-off exception.
